The black iron syndrome is simply a harbinger.

271
00:16:58,070 --> 00:17:00,330
Once it awakens, Japan—

272
00:17:00,330 --> 00:17:02,510
no, the entire world'll be turned upside-down.

273
00:17:02,950 --> 00:17:04,360
<i>This doesn't feel right...</i>

274
00:17:04,780 --> 00:17:07,730
<i>Feels like I'm in a strange dream, listening to Mahiro speak...</i>

275
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:11,740
Only one person is capable of stopping those idiots.

276
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:16,010
The family heiress and the most powerful mage known to man,

277
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,020
Kusaribe Hakaze.

278
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:20,340
<i>Yet for some reason,</i>

279
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:23,250
<i>I believe every word...</i>

280
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:25,210
The most powerful?

281
00:17:25,730 --> 00:17:28,900
Then are you that mage's apprentice or something?

282
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,050
Apprentice?

283
00:17:30,930 --> 00:17:33,260
Well, I'm helping her out.

284
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:37,600
<i>Hey, Mahiro...</i>

285
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:40,410
<i>This is a fair trade.</i>

286
00:17:40,410 --> 00:17:42,520
<i>You have no right to imply that I owe you any favors.</i>

287
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,520
You say that now, Hakaze,

288
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,970
but you're the one in trouble without me...

289
00:17:46,970 --> 00:17:48,130
Oh?

290
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:51,600
So you're saying you don't need me

291
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:54,990
