298
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,700
Mahiro!

299
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:23,790
One month ago,

300
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:26,520
I found a glass bottle washed up on the beach.

301
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:29,970
Inside was the doll and a piece of wood.

302
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,600
A message was written on it.

303
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,200
"If you believe in magic

304
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:37,320
and would trade your soul to have one wish granted,

305
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,330
hammer a nail into this doll."

306
00:18:40,740 --> 00:18:42,670
Even though this island is concealed,

307
00:18:42,670 --> 00:18:45,090
the ocean is still connected to the rest of the world.

308
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:48,750
The communication method used by oceanographers and castaways...

309
00:18:49,290 --> 00:18:51,000
A message in a bottle.

310
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,300
Even on a deserted island, I can find a bottle among the driftwood.

311
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:56,950
Once I cast my message out to sea,

312
00:18:56,950 --> 00:19:00,060
I just had to hope the right person would find it.

313
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:03,020
Guess I have some good luck, after all.

314
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:11,760
Samon,

315
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:14,900
